ometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized. B can be grumpy, can be uncooperative. C is known to be 100% reliable, creates a positive atmosphere with his crew. D is regarded as arrogant, relatively weak leadership skills.\n\nAgent 1 added: A is sometimes not good at taking criticism, can be unorganized (already have). Also they said \"Candidate A is regarded as a show-off\" and \"not open to new ideas\". Actually Agent 1's round 1 message included those as evidence from others. So we can reference.\n\nAgent 3 added: no extra beyond original.\n\nNow we need to evaluate best candidate.\n\nWe must weigh criteria: reliability, technical competence, calmness under pressure, cooperation, responsibility.\n\nLet's assess each candidate with all evidence:\n\nCandidate A:\n- Reliability: no explicit reliability; not conscientious; no mention of reliability. Could be questionable.\n- Technical competence: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, leadership qualities. Strong technical and situational awareness.\n- Calmness: not mentioned.\n- Cooperation: unfriendly, not good at taking criticism, unorganized, regarded as show-off, not open to new ideas, unfriendly. Many negatives.\n- Responsibility: leadership qualities, but also unorganized.\n\nOverall: strong technical but many cooperation issues and lack of reliability evidence.\n\nCandidate B:\n- Reliability: very conscientious (reliable), handles stress well (calmness), good at assessing weather, computer skills (technical). Also strong reliability.\n- Cooperation: pretentious, wrong tone, grumpy, uncooperative. Multiple negatives.\n- Responsibility: conscientious, handles stress, but no explicit leadership.\n- Technical: weather, computer, decent.\n\nOverall: strong reliability and calmness, but cooperation issues.\n\nCandidate C:\n- Reliability: known 100% reliable, creates positive atmosphere, puts concern for others above everything (cooperation), excellent attention skills, quick decisions (decision making). Strong reliability and cooperation.\n- Technical: quick decisions, attention skills, maybe not deep technical but good decision making. Understands complicated technology? Not in list but maybe not.\n- Cooperation: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education (negatives). But positive atmosphere and concern for others may offset.\n- Calmness: not explicit but quick correct decisions may imply calmness.\n- Responsibility: concern for others, positive atmosphere.\n\nOverall: strong reliability and crew atmosphere, some communication issues.\n\nCandidate D:\n- Reliability: takes responsibility seriously, responds to unexpected events adequately, solves problems extremely well, concentration. Good responsibility.\n- Cooperation: moody, loner, arrogant, weak leadership. Negative.\n- Technical: problem solving, concentration.\n- Calmness: responds to unexpected events adequately (some calmness).\n- Responsibility: strong.\n\nOverall: strong technical and responsibility but cooperation issues.\n\nThus the best balanced seems Candidate C, as Agent 1 argued. Candidate B also strong but cooperation issues severe. Candidate A technical but cooperation issues and lack reliability. Candidate D similar.\n\nThus as Agent 2, I should update my position to Candidate C, unless I think another candidate is better. I think C is best balanced.\n\nProvide confidence moderate.\n\nNow produce PUBLIC_MESSAGE with required structure, and METADATA_JSON with vote \"Candidate C\". Ensure agent field is \"agent_2\"."}
